    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_bycæw" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bycæw</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bucæw</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>спор</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>dispute</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>соревнование</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>competition</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">также</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">also</note><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>подпора</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> ("противостоящее")</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> ("opposite")</note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="ru">также</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"
                            >also</note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>support</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> ("противостоящее")</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> ("opposite")</note></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>dywwæ læǵy fæbycæw ysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>два человека заспорили</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>two people began to argue</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>isbucæw æncæ Dris æma Dengiz</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>заспорили Дрис и Денгиз</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Dris and Dengiz began to argue</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 47</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>næ sīs fenkʼ˳ystī, æmæ jæm bycæwtæ sæværdton</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>наша стена пошатнулась, и я приставил к ней подпоры</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>our wall staggered, and I leaned support against it</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из *%ibæcæw%i с перебоем %iæ%i → %iy%i | %iu%i под влиянием
                    губного, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_myd"/> и др. *%iBæcæw%i
                    сопоставляется с <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pačāw- (pčʼw-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>спор</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>раздор</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>68</biblScope></bibl>), из
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pat-čaw-</w>
                        <gloss><q>идти против</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>противодействовать</q></gloss></mentioned>; см. ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæwyn"/> ‘идти’. В осетинском ожидали бы в начале %if%i, а не
                    %ib%i; но ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bælas"/> ‘дерево’из *%ipalāsa%i-.
                    Может быть, имела место также контаминация со славянским <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">буча</w>
                        <gloss><q>шум</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ссора</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From *%ibæcæw%i with the transition %iæ%i → %iy%i | %iu%i
                    influenced by the labial like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_myn"/> etc.
                    *%iBæcæw%i is compared with <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pačāw- (pčʼw-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>dispute</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>discord</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>68</biblScope></bibl>), from
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*pat-čaw-</w>
                        <gloss><q>go against</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>oppose</q></gloss></mentioned>; see Ossetic <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæwyn"/> ‘go’. In Ossetic one would expect the initial %if%i
                    instead of %ib%i; but cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bælas"/> ‘tree’from
                    *%ipalāsa%i-. May be, the contamination with the Slavic <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w>buča</w>
                        <gloss><q>noise</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>quarrel</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.</etym>
            </entry>
